-- VEB May Buy Some Baikalsk Paper, Pulp Debts, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-05-21T04:27:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/veb-may-buy-some-baikalsk-paper-pulp-debts-vedomosti-says.html
VEB, Russia’s state development bank,
may buy out some of the debts of OAO Baikalsk Paper and Pulp
Mills to manage the mill’s bankruptcy,  Vedomosti  reported,
citing a government meeting led by  Igor Shuvalov , acting deputy
prime minister.  The amount to be bought by the bank is not disclosed, the
newspaper said.  Alfa Bank  is the biggest lender holding 51
percent of the mill’s debts and other big lenders include
companies affiliated with billionaire Oleg Deripaska’s Basic
Element that hold more than 600 million rubles ($19 million) of
debt, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
